init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he decided to try to trick the little pig into coming outside.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He found out that the little pig's favorite foods were pizza, beer, and ice cream.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was like, "hey little pig, I have some ingredients to make homemade pizza.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You want to come outside and help me make it?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I'm glad you decided to come outside.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was afraid you were going to be a stick in the mud about this."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The little pig laughed and said, "I'm not a stick in the mud.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm just smart enough to know that if I came outside, you'd eat me."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf said, "I'm glad you changed your mind.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: I'm glad you changed your mind.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Let's get started on making the pizzas."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Hey little pig, I just realized that I forgot to bring the pepperoni.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The moral of the story is that if you're a little pig, you should never trust a wolf.
